<div id="post-1154" class="cf post-1154 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/more-on-the-tivo-fast-foward-non-story/" title="More on the Tivo fast-foward non-story" rel="bookmark">More on the Tivo fast-foward non-story</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Nov</p>
			<p class="post-day">19</p>
			<p class="post-year">2004</p>				
		</div>

		This message board post from someone in Tivo product marketing clarifies what Tivo is and isn&#8217;t doing. It reinforces what I said earlier &#8212; Tivo showing banner ads when you fast-forward isn&#8217;t the end of the world.
		
	</div>

	<div class="post-footer">
		<a class="post-readmore" href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/more-on-the-tivo-fast-foward-non-story/" title="More on the Tivo fast-foward non-story">
