<div id="post-1153" class="cf post-1153 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/the-tivo-fast-forward-non-story/" title="The Tivo Fast-Forward Non-Story" rel="bookmark">The Tivo Fast-Forward Non-Story</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Nov</p>
			<p class="post-day">17</p>
			<p class="post-year">2004</p>				
		</div>

		According to Matt Haughey&#8217;s PVRblog, Tivo is updating its software to display advertisements while you fast-forward through programs. That&#8217;s right, you&#8217;ll see ads even while you fast-forward to skip the ads. People seem to think this is an abomination. What&#8217;s the big deal? Television has ads. There&#8217;s nothing evil in that; it&#8217;s just a business model. If you don&#8217;t like ads, you can sit and watch your home movies on ...
		
	</div>

	<div class="post-footer">
		<a class="post-readmore" href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/the-tivo-fast-forward-non-story/" title="The Tivo Fast-Forward Non-Story">
