	</div>
	
</div>

<div id="post-1151" class="cf post-1151 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/the-meaning-of-innovation/" title="The Meaning of Innovation" rel="bookmark">The Meaning of Innovation</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Nov</p>
			<p class="post-day">16</p>
			<p class="post-year">2004</p>				
		</div>

		I&#8217;m at a &#8220;Global Innovation Outlook&#8221; event organized by IBM in New York. Lots of great folks here, and &#8212; halleluja! &#8212; open WiFi in the auditorium at Rockefeller University. It&#8217;s too early to pass judgment on the program, but IBM is asking the right questions in exploring the nature of innovation in today&#8217;s world.
		
	</div>

	<div class="post-footer">
		<a class="post-readmore" href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/the-meaning-of-innovation/" title="The Meaning of Innovation">
		read more &rarr;</a>
