</div>

<div id="post-1149" class="cf post-1149 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/nirvana/" title="Nirvana" rel="bookmark">Nirvana</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Nov</p>
			<p class="post-day">12</p>
			<p class="post-year">2004</p>				
		</div>

		So here I am, sitting on a train, checking email, surfing the web, listening to a couple hundred songs, and blogging&#8230; all through my phone. I&#8217;ve had a Treo for more than a year, but this experience still gives me chills. Ten years ago there was, for all intents and purposes, no public Net. Five years from now, two billion people will be carrying it in their pockets. Crazy.
		
	</div>

	<div class="post-footer">
		<a class="post-readmore" href="http://werblog.com/2004/11/nirvana/" title="Nirvana">
		read more &rarr;</a>
